WEBVTT

00:01.186 --> 00:03.254
[chiming]

00:05.000 --> 00:11.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:20.606 --> 00:22.674
[piano playing ♪]

00:29.882 --> 00:32.083
[children singing]

00:32.116 --> 00:33.217
[Narrator] <i>Christmas.</i>

00:34.519 --> 00:36.721
<i>A time of good will and cheer</i>

00:36.755 --> 00:39.591
<i>celebrated by many all over the world.</i>

00:41.460 --> 00:43.427
<i>But, as Santa delivers presents</i>

00:43.462 --> 00:45.463
<i>to all of the good</i>
<i>girls and boys,</i>

00:45.497 --> 00:50.401
<i>there is an all but forgotten</i>
<i>tale of the yule Lord, Krampus.</i>

00:50.435 --> 00:53.437
<i>The Christmas Devil</i>
<i>and executioner of the wicked,</i>

00:53.472 --> 00:56.474
<i>is also the secretive brother</i>
<i>of St. Nick,</i>

00:56.508 --> 00:59.744
<i>whose job is the termination</i>
<i>of the lives of children</i>

00:59.778 --> 01:02.146
<i>that have done unexplainable</i>
<i>evil deeds</i>

01:02.180 --> 01:04.348
<i>without care or repercussion.</i>

01:04.382 --> 01:07.785
<i>But, as the new lists</i>
<i>of bad children are generated,</i>

01:07.820 --> 01:10.321
<i>Krampus only has</i>
<i>until the stroke of midnight</i>

01:10.355 --> 01:12.724
<i>on Christmas Eve</i>
<i>to complete his tasks.</i>

01:15.027 --> 01:17.428
<i>And so begins our story.</i>

01:20.265 --> 01:23.534
[distorted singing]

01:31.977 --> 01:33.577
[Jeremy, muffled]
Let me go!

01:34.713 --> 01:36.114
Help!

01:36.749 --> 01:39.416
♪ ♪

01:44.923 --> 01:47.125
[yelling] Ahh!

01:48.193 --> 01:50.128
Ahh!

01:53.866 --> 01:55.566
Ahh!

01:57.469 --> 01:59.103
Ahh!

02:07.880 --> 02:10.148
[rock music ♪]

02:13.418 --> 02:14.952
♪ ♪

02:44.083 --> 02:46.851
[ominous ambience]

02:53.759 --> 02:57.095
Listen, I told you.
It's not like him.

02:58.396 --> 03:01.298
We don't want him
to end up like the others.

03:03.936 --> 03:05.103
[door squeaks]

03:09.304 --> 03:10.469
Jeremy!

03:11.744 --> 03:15.546
Jeremy! Where have you been?
- Was that Jeremy?

03:15.580 --> 03:17.782
Yeah, he-he just came in.
He's upstairs.

03:23.321 --> 03:25.823
[creepy Christmas music ♪]

03:38.203 --> 03:43.474
♪ ♪

04:04.362 --> 04:06.330
Jeremy, where were you?

04:07.532 --> 04:10.501
Jeremy, are you all right?
Jeremy, answer your mother.

04:10.535 --> 04:11.702
Jeremy, answer your mother.
[phone ringing]

04:11.736 --> 04:12.736
[fading]
Jeremy, answer your mother.

04:12.771 --> 04:15.539
Answer your mother.
[ringing continues]

04:15.573 --> 04:18.176
[goth-rock music ♪]

04:25.583 --> 04:30.554
Hey, Captain.
Another one?

04:32.057 --> 04:34.859
All right, I'll be in
in ten minutes.

04:34.893 --> 04:37.128
♪ ♪

04:50.775 --> 04:53.077
[coffee pouring]

04:57.149 --> 04:58.149
[Rebecca]
You're up early.

04:58.183 --> 05:01.418
What's wrong?
There was another.

05:01.453 --> 05:03.387
Where?
Not far.

05:03.421 --> 05:06.390
[sighs]
And right before Christmas.

05:07.392 --> 05:09.160
I can't even imagine.

05:11.563 --> 05:12.897
I'm going to be late.

05:14.499 --> 05:19.570
Duff, wait.
Just make sure you come home.

05:26.345 --> 05:27.845
[sighs]

05:38.924 --> 05:41.325
[goth-rock music ♪]

05:45.163 --> 05:48.532
♪ ♪

08:27.692 --> 08:28.825
[engine shuts off]

08:32.030 --> 08:33.264
[door closes]

08:41.905 --> 08:43.274
[door squeaks]

09:07.799 --> 09:08.999
[sighs]

09:11.570 --> 09:12.803
[Captain Farabee] Yeah?

09:15.173 --> 09:17.341
Good morning, Captain.
How are you doing, kid?

09:17.375 --> 09:20.644
Good.
All right, what do we have?

09:20.678 --> 09:26.283
Same area. Concentrated here.
Cambridge Springs.

09:26.318 --> 09:27.784
That's where all the kids
are coming up missing.

09:27.819 --> 09:30.954
Mm-hmm.
Centrally located, obscure.

09:30.989 --> 09:32.022
It makes sense.

09:33.791 --> 09:34.958
You know, it's been ten years

09:34.993 --> 09:37.161
since we've saw something
like this in this region.

09:37.195 --> 09:40.030
What are you saying?
Are you saying serial killer?

09:40.064 --> 09:42.566
Or something like that.
Take a look at this.

09:48.740 --> 09:50.274
Toronto.
Uh-huh.

09:50.308 --> 09:53.310
Kids coming up missing.
Body parts found.

09:53.345 --> 09:55.045
Traced back to a year ago.

09:55.079 --> 09:57.381
Same time all of these
abductions happened.

09:57.415 --> 09:59.517
The same thing happened
ten years earlier.

09:59.551 --> 10:01.051
It's been all over the world.

10:01.853 --> 10:02.719
There's something bigger here

10:02.754 --> 10:05.022
than we can ever imagine
going on.

10:05.056 --> 10:07.358
All over the world?
Yeah.

10:07.392 --> 10:08.859
Looking all over the world?

10:08.893 --> 10:11.162
[sad music ♪]

10:11.196 --> 10:13.630
Does this have anything to do
with your own abduction maybe?

10:15.233 --> 10:18.269
Does it?
That's a long time ago, kid.

10:21.406 --> 10:22.573
Does it?

10:25.277 --> 10:26.710
I remember that night.

10:27.712 --> 10:29.580
Your father and I were working

10:29.614 --> 10:32.416
undercover trying to get
these bad guys from Buffalo,

10:32.450 --> 10:34.151
and your mom called.

10:34.186 --> 10:36.687
Like she called
a million times before.

10:36.721 --> 10:38.755
And he went home
like a million times before.

10:40.091 --> 10:42.059
And that's the last time
I saw him alive.

10:43.461 --> 10:46.096
He was a good man.
Yeah, he was.

10:46.130 --> 10:51.368
And he was a good cop.
Me, Crazy Harry.

10:51.403 --> 10:54.004
[chuckles]  The three of us
were inseparable.

10:56.608 --> 10:58.942
Grab some men, scour the area.

10:58.976 --> 11:00.877
I'll assemble a team tonight.

11:00.912 --> 11:02.012
We'll hit it first thing
in the morning.

11:02.046 --> 11:03.380
We'll check all of those regions
out there

11:03.415 --> 11:04.281
that we've been talking about.

11:04.316 --> 11:05.616
We're gonna get him this time.

11:05.650 --> 11:06.983
I want this fucker.

11:07.018 --> 11:08.752
We'll get him this time,
Captain.

11:08.786 --> 11:11.922
I know. There's one more thing.

11:11.956 --> 11:14.692
Yeah.
That scumbag, Brian Hatt.

11:14.726 --> 11:15.593
Yeah?

11:15.627 --> 11:16.760
He was released
from prison yesterday.

11:16.794 --> 11:17.861
How could he get out?

11:17.895 --> 11:19.162
It's been ten years.
- I know it's been ten years.

11:19.197 --> 11:20.531
I don't know, a loophole?

11:20.565 --> 11:22.833
These scumbag lawyers,
they don't give a shit.

11:22.867 --> 11:24.101
He said he was going
to come for you.

11:24.135 --> 11:26.270
I want you to watch your ass,
do you understand me?

11:26.304 --> 11:28.572
I'll watch my back.
You're a good cop.

11:28.607 --> 11:30.807
Your dad would be proud of you.
Thank you.

11:30.842 --> 11:32.809
Thanks for the head's up.
You be careful.

11:32.844 --> 11:33.677
We'll get him, Captain.

11:35.680 --> 11:37.748
I want that fuck!

11:37.782 --> 11:38.882
[door closes]

11:40.184 --> 11:42.653
[chattering]
[rock music ♪]

11:43.755 --> 11:45.556
Hey, Jack and Coke, please.

11:50.194 --> 11:51.562
[ice rattling]

11:59.537 --> 12:00.537
Thank you.

12:03.475 --> 12:05.108
Hey, can you get these guys

12:05.143 --> 12:06.810
comin' in a Bud Light
and Miller Light?

12:08.513 --> 12:09.747
♪ ♪

12:11.783 --> 12:12.783
Hey guys.

12:12.817 --> 12:14.485
Grab your beer and meet me
at the table.

12:16.921 --> 12:17.921
Have a seat.

12:18.823 --> 12:20.324
[John]
You wanted to see us?

12:20.358 --> 12:23.026
All right,
we've got a situation here.

12:23.060 --> 12:24.828
The dead kid from the lake,
right?

12:24.862 --> 12:28.599
Yeah, I've been chasing
these missing kids forever.

12:28.633 --> 12:30.634
That-that's all I do any more.

12:30.669 --> 12:32.603
It's what I've been working on
my entire career.

12:34.606 --> 12:37.841
Look, I know where he is.
At least the area anyway.

12:39.243 --> 12:40.477
The captain has given us

12:40.512 --> 12:43.681
full authorization to use
whatever force necessary.

12:43.715 --> 12:46.249
Now, if this guy
follows the same pattern,

12:46.284 --> 12:49.553
he's going to stop
Christmas Eve night,

12:49.587 --> 12:51.087
and we're going to lose him.

12:51.122 --> 12:52.956
So, we have to get him
right away.

12:54.759 --> 12:55.859
We're here to help, Duff.

12:56.695 --> 12:59.496
You take this so personally,
man.

12:59.531 --> 13:02.466
It's a job, right?
It's an important job, right?

13:03.768 --> 13:06.370
But there's nothing
that any of us can do,

13:06.404 --> 13:09.540
ever, to bring those
dead babies back.

13:10.775 --> 13:13.677
Okay.
You guys need to hear this.

13:17.349 --> 13:20.083
I was a, uh, I was a bad kid.

13:21.786 --> 13:25.456
I did things...I wish I could
take back and I can't.

13:28.159 --> 13:32.463
One day, I was walking to school
and I got abducted.

13:34.098 --> 13:37.033
I don't remember much.
I must've been knocked out.

13:37.068 --> 13:38.569
I was in and out
of consciousness.

13:39.671 --> 13:42.773
But what I do remember
is being terrified.

13:42.807 --> 13:45.275
When I came to,
I was under water,

13:45.309 --> 13:48.812
in a bag, in a frozen lake.

13:50.948 --> 13:52.249
I don't know how I got out.

13:53.251 --> 13:54.551
But, somehow
I got out of the water

13:54.586 --> 13:56.653
and as I was running home

13:56.688 --> 13:58.555
not sure if he was going
to catch me again,

13:58.590 --> 14:00.257
if I'd ever see
my parents again,

14:01.292 --> 14:03.660
I promised myself
that I'd change my ways.

14:04.763 --> 14:08.465
Guys, it was 30 years ago.
This is the same guy.

14:10.402 --> 14:14.137
[Bob] You got taken, too?
- What do you mean, "too?"

14:14.171 --> 14:15.639
It's just a dream.

14:15.673 --> 14:19.543
A reoccurring dream
that keeps coming back, man.

14:19.577 --> 14:22.312
[John] So, do you think
it's the same guy?

14:24.081 --> 14:25.982
Yeah, it's-it's the same M.O.,

14:26.984 --> 14:28.786
the same timing,
the same motive.

14:29.621 --> 14:30.687
It's him.

14:31.122 --> 14:33.290
All right, one more thing, guys.

14:33.324 --> 14:37.127
Um, Brian Hatt got released
from prison yesterday.

14:37.161 --> 14:40.497
Some lawyer got him off
on a technicality, I'm not sure.

14:42.667 --> 14:44.267
[Bob]
What? I know.

14:44.302 --> 14:45.469
[Bob sarcastically chuckles]

14:46.971 --> 14:52.042
It's bullshit, but he's out.
Now, wait a minute.

14:52.076 --> 14:53.176
He threatens you,

14:53.210 --> 14:56.847
he threatens your family
and somehow this guy gets out?

14:56.881 --> 14:58.214
Yeah, I know, look.

14:58.249 --> 15:00.551
I don't know the details
right now.

15:00.585 --> 15:02.018
He just got out,

15:02.053 --> 15:04.655
he's going to want to revel
in his new found freedom.

15:04.689 --> 15:06.022
He's not going
to cause us a problem.

15:06.057 --> 15:08.191
Right now, we have
to concentrate on this.

15:08.225 --> 15:10.994
We put him on the back burner,
all right?

15:11.028 --> 15:13.564
All that time, all that work,
all that energy.

15:14.766 --> 15:15.766
Wasted.

15:17.635 --> 15:20.671
I know, I know.
Couple more beers, please?

15:25.743 --> 15:27.511
Thanks, baby.
Mm-hmm.

15:29.747 --> 15:33.183
All right, guys.
Here are your packets.

15:33.217 --> 15:36.386
They have GPS coordinates.
Protocols.

15:37.555 --> 15:40.190
Tomorrow morning we meet
at seven a.m. at the station.

15:40.224 --> 15:41.925
Be ready to go, okay?
[John] You got it.

15:41.960 --> 15:45.696
Okay. All right, Duff.
Hey, make this your last one.

15:45.730 --> 15:47.063
I need you fresh in the morning.

15:47.098 --> 15:49.299
[country music ♪]

15:53.337 --> 15:54.471
Hey, Duff.
Yeah.

15:54.506 --> 15:58.475
What's up, buddy?
[sighs] Did you see his face?

15:59.978 --> 16:01.044
No.

16:02.714 --> 16:08.118
He's...It's-it's...
I-it's not human.

16:09.086 --> 16:13.289
Yeah, I know...
Tomorrow, man.

16:13.324 --> 16:14.558
Tomorrow.
All right.

16:14.592 --> 16:16.459
♪ ♪

16:21.966 --> 16:24.100
So, what's the deal with Duffin?

16:24.135 --> 16:26.737
As far as?
Why's he do this?

16:26.771 --> 16:28.739
Didn't his dad leave him
some fortune?

16:28.773 --> 16:29.840
He came into some money.

16:29.874 --> 16:31.975
Something from his grandfather,
from what I heard.

16:32.010 --> 16:35.078
But, his dad did the job
the same way, man.

16:35.112 --> 16:36.279
Wasn't for the money.

16:37.782 --> 16:40.216
And what's up with this ex con?

16:40.251 --> 16:42.218
Brian Hatt?
Yeah.

16:42.253 --> 16:45.088
Yeah, guy's a shit bag,
all right.

16:45.122 --> 16:48.458
He's an armed robber.
Um, I was working him on that.

16:48.492 --> 16:50.193
And then, he takes a kid.

16:50.227 --> 16:53.129
Kidnaps a kid for ransom,
that's when Duff came in.

16:54.599 --> 16:56.633
And it's--I don't know,
it was a while back.

16:56.668 --> 16:58.969
Uh, Duff has him
on this rape case,

16:59.003 --> 17:01.738
and then, you know,
evidence was thin, it was weak,

17:01.773 --> 17:03.206
didn't really hold up in court.

17:05.175 --> 17:06.542
We should probably
get out of here.

17:06.578 --> 17:07.609
All right.

17:13.718 --> 17:19.189
So, rich guy with a vendetta.
Always a dangerous combination.

17:19.223 --> 17:21.858
♪ ♪

17:32.470 --> 17:34.972
[footsteps approaching]

17:35.006 --> 17:39.843
♪ ♪

17:39.877 --> 17:40.978
[Santa Claus]
It's the 22nd.

17:41.012 --> 17:42.646
You have two days left.

17:43.748 --> 17:45.983
Scratch Brad Myers
off the naughty list.

17:46.017 --> 17:47.584
He's gone good on us.

17:49.887 --> 17:52.756
Sean Roberts, Heather Duffin,

17:53.758 --> 17:55.391
move them to the top
of the list.

17:55.426 --> 17:57.861
Top priority. Do you understand?

17:57.895 --> 18:00.831
[Krampus, hoarse]  Yes, Nicholas.
- Are you okay?

18:00.865 --> 18:02.398
Yes.

18:04.401 --> 18:08.972
Okay, remember,
Sean Roberts and Duffin.

18:09.007 --> 18:13.176
Top of the priority list.
I'll see you on the eve.

18:13.210 --> 18:14.544
All right, my brother.

18:24.722 --> 18:25.622
[door opens]

18:25.657 --> 18:28.391
[ominous ambience]

18:29.060 --> 18:30.193
[door closes]

18:39.871 --> 18:41.038
[corkscrew squeaks]

18:45.109 --> 18:46.076
[corkscrew squeaks]

18:46.110 --> 18:49.579
[ghostly sounds]

19:14.806 --> 19:16.673
[techno music ♪]

19:28.352 --> 19:30.087
♪ ♪

19:35.827 --> 19:36.860
[lock clicks]

19:42.499 --> 19:45.202
[echoes of children
playing and laughing]

19:53.244 --> 19:56.146
[continued echoes of children
playing and laughing]

20:41.525 --> 20:43.593
[dark music ♪]

20:52.670 --> 20:54.204
Jeremy!

20:54.238 --> 20:55.405
Go.

20:55.439 --> 20:58.341
I want this motherfucker,
do you understand me?

20:58.375 --> 21:02.378
You get him.
[fading] You get him.

21:02.413 --> 21:04.514
♪ ♪

21:16.760 --> 21:17.928
[chamber clicks]

21:22.200 --> 21:23.233
It's you or me.

21:26.070 --> 21:27.270
[gun clicks]

21:29.573 --> 21:31.274
[sighs]

21:37.215 --> 21:39.216
♪ ♪

21:44.755 --> 21:45.755
[gun clicks]

21:46.324 --> 21:49.993
[dark ambience]

22:15.019 --> 22:19.756
♪ ♪

22:55.759 --> 22:57.160
[ambience]

22:58.362 --> 23:00.430
Hey, I saw you take $20. That's cheating.
- I-I did not.

23:00.464 --> 23:01.831
Yes, you did.

23:01.865 --> 23:04.434
I'm not playing this stupid game anymore.
- [Sean's Mom] Aw, come--

23:04.468 --> 23:07.503
What the heck?
Why do you guys want to fight?

23:07.538 --> 23:09.072
I'm sorry, kids.

23:12.576 --> 23:14.377
There's somebody outside.

23:15.579 --> 23:18.381
[creepy music ♪]

23:21.185 --> 23:22.385
[Sean's Mom]
Let me see.

23:23.955 --> 23:26.622
No, it's okay.
I don't see anybody.

23:26.657 --> 23:29.125
[phone ringing]
They were just there.

23:29.160 --> 23:30.961
Probably just a shadow.

23:31.929 --> 23:34.297
[phone continues to ring]
Hello?

23:34.332 --> 23:38.634
Okay.
Sean, can you take me home?

23:38.669 --> 23:39.735
Yeah.

23:42.006 --> 23:43.606
[Sean's Mom]
Come right back.

23:45.276 --> 23:47.944
[tense ambience]

23:52.149 --> 23:54.851
♪ ♪

23:54.885 --> 23:57.587
[distant chatting]

24:22.880 --> 24:25.781
Well, bye, Sean.
Bye.

24:34.992 --> 24:37.727
♪ ♪

24:41.499 --> 24:43.433
[bells jiggling]

25:00.584 --> 25:03.920
[bells jiggling]

25:10.794 --> 25:12.495
♪ ♪

25:24.341 --> 25:28.178
[John breathing heavily]

25:33.084 --> 25:34.384
[John] It's too early for this.

25:34.418 --> 25:35.451
I need more coffee.

25:36.287 --> 25:37.820
[Jeremy]
Guys, get your weapons prepped.

25:37.854 --> 25:40.823
Magazine. Magazines.

25:51.768 --> 25:54.170
[intense music ♪]

26:02.279 --> 26:04.347
[snow crushing under footsteps]

26:07.384 --> 26:09.986
♪ ♪

27:15.952 --> 27:17.053
[branch breaks]

27:43.280 --> 27:44.334
[whispering] This is the lake

27:44.348 --> 27:46.849
where they found the body
last night of the kid.

27:46.883 --> 27:50.019
Couple of fishermen
were out here and found it.

27:50.053 --> 27:53.256
There's a bunch of abandoned
houses out here and caves.

27:53.290 --> 27:54.790
I think he's holed up
in this area.

27:56.660 --> 27:59.128
Let's go around and see
what we can find.

27:59.162 --> 28:01.931
We'll work our way up to the
area where he was taken.

28:01.965 --> 28:03.132
All right, let's go.

28:14.111 --> 28:15.712
♪ ♪

28:16.513 --> 28:19.048
[creepy howling]

28:29.760 --> 28:32.328
Hey boss, you're going to want
to look at this.

28:32.363 --> 28:33.730
[Jeremy]
What do you got?

28:33.764 --> 28:35.665
Too fresh to be from last night.

28:42.740 --> 28:45.341
[distorted screeching]

28:54.518 --> 28:58.688
[Bob] Duff, this is getting dragged
away from the lake.

28:58.722 --> 29:01.691
All right,
let's follow the trail.

29:10.467 --> 29:11.534
[tense ambience]

29:11.568 --> 29:12.769
[distorted rewind-sound]

29:36.627 --> 29:37.927
[distorted rewind-sound]

29:38.729 --> 29:39.962
What is that?

29:41.398 --> 29:43.199
It's him, it's him.
[Jeremy] Open fire!

29:43.233 --> 29:46.469
[rock music ♪]

29:57.214 --> 29:59.982
Where the fuck did he go?
Did you guys hit him?

30:01.518 --> 30:03.553
Get a magazine.
Get a magazine.

30:03.587 --> 30:04.587
Come on guys.

30:06.457 --> 30:08.023
Spread out. Let's go.

30:10.361 --> 30:13.463
[intense ambience]

